rComments: One of my favourite classes ive ever taken. Not the easiest class and you will 100% need to go to class and do the work, but you'll never be bored. Tests are hard but reflect what was taught in class. Id take class with him again in a heartbeat.

By far the worst prof ever. He can single you out and make you feel dumb and he is not willing to help you even when you try to show that you are making an effort. Getting him to meet with you can take weeks as he always pushes the date back and he is also a hypocrite who is insensitive and does not understand how to properly mark your work at all.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Tough grader', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: Made Managerial my favourite class!!

Straight up Fkin Legend. Favourite prof of all time at uOttawa. Absolutely hilarious and cares a lot about his students. He makes up stories about how to tweets at sports stars such as Tiger Woods and how they respond with inspirational quotes. Legend. It is an absolute pure pleasure to take Fodil's course. This isn't a joke. Must take prof.

Prof Fodil cares a lot about student's grades. When I messed up the midterm exam, I thought I would get a very low mark since everyone said that the final was brutal. However, the final was actually acceptable and I eventually got a B for the class(I could've got an A if I did well in the midterm). Going to his class is absolutely necessary!
The final will mess you up.

There's no such thing as going to class and then you will be blessed, but prof Fodil provides good resources for your midterm(although I almost failed, can't really blame him) and if you are willing to pay extra effort then your midterm will be fine. Don't know about the final, but it is going to be tough as far as I can see.
Just show up to class, listen to what he says and practice the booklet he gives you and you'll be blessed

Fodil is a great prof. I was nervous because in the first lecture he asked so many questions and has a thick accent, but as the semester went on I barely noticed the accent and the participation made you pay attention. Final was garbage though. I studied everything he taught and it wasn't enough. I think that's the class though and not him.
THE BEST PROF I NEVER HAD. Le cours est un pure plaisir.

Professeur Adjaoud à le don de garder ses élèves attentifs durant un cours de comptabilité et de rendre des concepts assez complexes très simple. Le mi-session est facile mais attention à l'examen final; étudiez surtout dans son recueil pour l'examen de mi-session et concentrer vous sur le manuel du cours pour l'examen final.
This guy is the best accounting prof ever. His $20 textbook is literally all you will ever need.

Really great teacher. If you practice past midterms you will do great on the midterm. However, the final was extremely hard so be prepared. Very engaging lectures and asks you questions during class so you are forced to pay attention.

Incredible prof. Truly cares about making sure his students understand the material. Explains things well and in a way that makes it easy to understand. His accent can be difficult to understand at times, so you really have to pay attention. The course itself sucks, but he makes it less sucky. Don't need the textbook, but will need his course pack.

Best accounting prof ever! He really makes his lectures interesting. You need to buy the notebook he wrote or else you won't be able to follow in class and do the homework and practice exams. He explains really well the subject and answers questions in class for everyone to benefit the explanations. I definitely recommend taking his class!

M. Adjaoud est sans hésiter le meilleur professeur que j'ai reçu dans mon parcours universitaire. Il savait comment capter l'attention des étudiants en donnant des lectures interactives. Les examens prennent du temps à compléter considérant qu'il y a beaucoup de matière sur ceux-ci, mais en étant bien préparé il n'y aura aucun problème.

The first couple lectures will make you nervous because his accent and style takes a little time to get used to, but he is the best managerial accounting prof in the school bar none. Exceptional lecture depth and explanations, and his course pack is the best Ive ever used and is also cheap. Extremely understanding and cares about your grade.

Loved having Fodil. Lectures are very interesting, fun, and interactive. Final exam was impossible, there was a big bell-curve, a BIG one. Takes accounting, and actually makes it surprisingly fun (and I absolutely hate accounting). Recommend him 100%.

Fodil made this class so easy it's crazy. His accent takes some getting used to, but he goes through all the examples in the course-pack super slowly (too slow, really) and has extremely clear expectations for tests, quizzes, and the final. Seriously, there's no excuse for doing poorly. He's also a nice, quirky guy. Don't get caught on your phone.

The best prof I've ever had in my 3 years at Telfer. I re took this course to get a better grade and having him as my prof made me understand Accounting so much better. He cares so much about his students and is always there to help, and he takes things step by step all the time. Pay attention in class & you will do great! Highly recommend Fodil!!

Great professor but awful when it comes to needing help. I went to see him 3 times asking for help and every single time, he told me to just go back through my notes and try myself. The whole reason I went to see him in the first place is because I did not understand the content by myself.
Do what he asks you to and you will pass ! if not easy fail.

Ce prof est difficile à évaluer : il est très drôle, est bien organisé, utilise un recueil de 12 $ et non un manuel inutile, puis connaît bien la matière.  Cependant, sa méthode d'enseignement laisse à désirer... Souvent, le contenu n'est pas clair, ses notes de cours sont incomplètes, puis intimide ceux qui ne participe pas / n'ont pas le recueil.

This one of the few accounting profs that is good in Teller. He is easier than the other profs teaching this course in my opinion. He makes you understand the material and the quizzes are not hard at all. The only thing is that he played us during the the final , the final was kind of difficult.

He is a good professor ;however, he can be very rude to you sometimes and will not give you any hints on the final. He just tell you everything that on the book that he wrote will be tested . You need to be prepared to be surprised for the final. Final exam is tough and not fair. Even if you get all you exam As, that will not help you in the final
He is a really good teacher. He is dynamic, teachs well.

Hands down, Fodil is one of the best profs I've had at the University. He is very clear when he teaches the subject material! It is clear he is passionate about teaching in the way he engages students and is funny while doing it. The final is hard but it is standardized so it does not matter who your prof is.

Amazing teacher, for the first time since im in university I did not need to open a manual since he explained everything so clearly.  Everyone whos complaining about the final exam are just used to have everything given to them easily, if they fully understood the theory they would have done good.

His test before final exam was easy to get a A and above;however, his final exam was crucial.I mean, SUPER DIFFICULT. I did not expect that in the lecture; he did not mention what would be the key points that would be tested in the final exam, which made the final extremely harsh for everyone.

I have mixed views about this professor. He did a great job at teaching us everything, he isn't super clear with a thick accent, but he'll do better than most profs. However, he can be very rude to you, hes not the nicest guy out there. And the final exam was extremely difficult, he lied to us about whats coming which is where I was shocked.

His final was crucial and it was not closely related to the course pack and textbook It was like you expected what would be on the test However the actual final exam was out of everyone's expectations

Really nerdy professor, explains extremely slow. His course pack notes are really useful but some explanations you need to attend class in order since not everything is in the course pack. Midterm was easier than final. Final had almost impossible multiple choices and questions completely different than seen in class with full of tricks.
His lectures were very clear, and used a coursepack that gave you all the slides at once. He was willing to answer questions by email and help, especially if he can tell you go to class.

I was seriously thinking of switching to accounting just because of this professor. Hands down, one of the best professors in the faculty. Anyone would be lucky to have him (even if you have no intention of specializing in accounting)

His course pack was amazing,  better than the actual textbook. He explains things really well. As long as you pay attention in class, everything makes sense and he guides you through the process of finding the answers. I wasn't interested in accounting but found myself looking forward to this class. It's a shame not many other profs are like him.

Amazing teacher!!!! Il est passionné par la matière et n'a pas peur de nous partager son intêret! Il est très clair dans ses explications et fais participer la classe. Le final vaut 60%, mais si tu vas à tout ses cours et prends des bonnes notes, il facile d'avoir au dessus de B.

He is an amazing professor that actually makes you want to go to class. He is very clear in his explanations and wants his students to understand, therefore will explain it in different ways. Very Helpful! His "textbook" is actually a course pack and it is the best thing ever for accounting!
Best teacher in Telfer
Tells students to "go home and make pleasure with accounting."
He is nice but the final exam has killed me.
My favourite prof of all time! He's such a sweetheart and very funny. He simplifies everything! Very easy to get an A in this class, just don't neglect it. "Kif kif" I recommend!!!

Probably the BEST teacher I've had. Class is interesting and he's a very motivating teacher (maybe because he randomly picks people in class to answer questions). He's also super funny! His exams are fair, if you studied the little note book he makes and went to class, you'll be fine.
Simply the best Professor, best teacher at Telfer. The world will be a better place if he thought all of the finance and accounting courses!
Très bon prof
le meilleur prof de Telfer, il est tellement drole!

Vraiment un mauvais professeur, fais souvent des blagues plates et passe beaucoup de temps à parler de lui même au lieu d'enseigner la matière. N'utilise pas les mêmes termes que dans le manuels donc peut souvent porter à confusion. Parles souvent aux étudiants comme s'ils sont en maternelle (ex: "fouillons dans notre boître à outil").

Best accounting teacher! Gives great lectures in ADM2341!  He's extremely funny! Warning: Final exam would be hard. But you just have to understand accounting concepts and study regularly to succeed. If you don't understand anything in ADM2341, ask him, he'll help you. Also, PRACTICE! 95% hand work, 5% genius!

He's a very clear prof and material on exams cover what was seen in class (even though final is always tough for this class). Having said that I found him very arrogant and unwilling to help the 2 times I went to his office despite the fact that I was good student.
I hate accounting, but this prof literally made me realize its usefulness and made me actually enjoy it. Never thought it would happen.

Hands down one of the best professors at the university.  His course pack for the class is fantastic, really helped my learning style and overall was better than the textbook, honestly wish I hadn't bought the textbook.  He calls people out for using their cells which makes you want to pay attention.  Overall awesome professor.

Hands down best prof I've ever had. All you need is his little 7$ note package and to actually go to class and you'll be great. He's really scary the first class ("if you don't have the syllabus printed you should leave."), but it's completely worth it. TAKE HIS CLASS.

He actually goes slow and takes the time to make sure you understand the content and the method. Extremely helpful. Textbook is for practice only but he also gives his own practice problems in class and solves with the class to make sure you understand. Takes time to prepare students for exams.
good professor for ADM2341

Monsieur Adjaoud est un excellent prof! Il rend un cours qui pourrait etre vraiment ennuyant, VRAIMENT interessant! Il sait gaerder l'attention et fait rire tout le monde! Il est le seule prof que j'ai vue la classe l'applaudir a la fin de l'anner! Tout ses examen son facile sauf pour le finale! Il faut vraiment etre pret, croyez moi!
great prof who makes learning the subject easy and for the most part clear. anyone who frequently relates material to tiger woods/daniel alfredson is the man. he truly has a passion for what he does.
This guy is the best guy of all the guys I have had be guys and teach me. He talks about couscous and isn't afraid to be better than most. I love him.

Excellent professor. Motivates all students to be interested in the subject while subject is not the most popular with students (accounting, finance). Extremely inspirational. Great mentor. Anyone would be lucky to have him as a professor.

While his accent makes him almost completely incomprehensible he's probably the best prof for this course. His midterms were very similar to previous years and all the material in the exams and quizzes reflect material. You don't really need the textbooks, his notes are enough. The only reason to go to class is to get the answers to the capstones
GOOD PROF,  EASY CLASS , FINAL WAS A BIT CHALLENGING. OVERALL, GREAT PROF, GOOD COURSE. YOU DON'T REALLY NEED TEXTBOOK THOUGH, HIS NOTES WERE EVERYTHING.
Excellent teacher.  He teached me in ADM 2750 and ADM 2741 and he explains everything so everybody understands.  You will learn a lot with him.  The exams are hard tho.
Best teacher ever. Plit, competent, easy teaching. Highly recommanded.

C'est le prof le mieux payer de Telfer school of management, une chose que je n'ai pas encore comprise vu que c'est l'un des pire profs que je n'ai jamais vu dans a la faculte de gestion. Je vous decris: L'arogance absolue+ Old school teaching = Adjaoud. Ce prof s'attend a ce que vous connaisser les reponses sans meme faire le cours.
Excellent and very nice professor
Great professor.
Excellent teacher!
No Comments
